<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=PVP&message.id=427#M427">53</a> of 127
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 512 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>
<P>Hi Trynd,</P>
<P>Regarding your first post I fully agree with points 1 - 3. However, I disagree with points 4) &amp; 5) so would like to address these.</P>
<P><EM>4.) item loot upon death.</EM></P>
<P>Unfortunately item loot is too harsh to actually encourage most players into PvP. As you know pure Melees MUST have decent gear in nearly all their slots simply to compete on an even footing with casters. Coupled with the fact people can (and will) get ganked by groups while solo, I can understand why people don't like this particular rule. Players want to PvP not continuely PvE because they keep losing hard earned gear to keep up.</P><B>
<P>I'd rather find another way to directly reward PvP victors and punish the victims. Perhaps a TIME BASED penalty, where you are sent back to your bind with all you gear upon a PvP death but are unable to enter the zone of your death for say 5hours. This would really give the victors a feeling of reward, and at higher levels the winning guild could continue to raid without the typical zerg + training from the losers. The idea needs tweaking but you get the picture.....</P></B>
<P><EM>5.) PvP within 20 lvl limit</EM></P>
<P>While I despise grievers and green farms I strongly disagree with PvP being limited to within lvl20s only. Why? because I hate invul. healers, bards and spies etc more. Its far more annoying to lose a fight because an even opponent has a untouchable bard giving him selo's or red healer keeping him alive than being ganked during lower levels by green farmers.</P>
<P>I believe with 2 well balance sides you could encourage Team Play anyway, so grievers/farmers will be policed better.</P>
<P><EM>iss.</EM></P></DIV>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
		<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
