<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=PVP&message.id=433#M433">55</a> of 127
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 492 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<P>Darren,</P>
<P>Thanks for the response.&nbsp; Regarding your point:</P>
<P><EM>4.) item loot upon death.</EM></P>
<DIV>
<P><EM>Unfortunately item loot is too harsh to actually encourage most players into PvP. As you know pure Melees MUST have decent gear in nearly all their slots simply to compete on an even footing with casters. Coupled with the fact people can (and will) get ganked by groups while solo, I can understand why people don't like this particular rule. Players want to PvP not continuely PvE because they keep losing hard earned gear to keep up.</EM></P>
<P>Pre-Luclin, pure melees were very competitive in pvp (especially during the Kunark era) as long as they had a decent weapon and one essential stat: MR.&nbsp; All other resists were inconsequential relative to the importance of MR.&nbsp; For a server that is to be old world only, I think it would make sense for resists to be changed to the way that they were before the re-adjustment (if possible) due to the difficulty in getting multiple resists to the 100+ range.&nbsp; Even with full BD gear, resists will be just around that 100ish range, and debuffs at their normal strength would make most people vulnerable.&nbsp; If my memory serves it wasn't until Luclin that resists (and to a much greater extent, HP gear) started getting out of hand.&nbsp; </P>
<P>I played a monk up all throughout the Kunark and Velious eras, and I was extremelly deadly - even without ever owning a Tstaff.&nbsp; I simply was very good at jousting and had&nbsp;relatively high MR (80-110ish depending on when).&nbsp; Later on in the life of a server, when jewelry becomes available, melees will be able to get sufficient amounts of MR to resist snare/root (which is the central goal of all resist gear) if the resists are returned to how they were to where they can be very competitive with casters - and indoors they'll still do extremelly well.</P>
<P>Initially in the life of the server, yes, melees would probably be less common than casters, but melees would still be very effective when grouped and as all PvE powergamers know, melees are very key in PvE; many groups of players would likely go into the server with predetermined PLing plans (similar to SZ when it came up).&nbsp; Item loot will encourage teamwork with your team/guildmates to an even greater extent then on SZ, and in the long run is necessary to encourage pvp.&nbsp; </P>
<P>Even if the server is a perpetual caster gankfest - like Discord was - that would be fun!&nbsp; (It wouldn't be though)</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P></DIV>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
