			>
			<DIV><FONT size=2>
<P>Yes Trynd, having played mostly pure melees or hybrids myself I would also agree that they do become balanced enough with good MR. And a smart player who is able to joust becomes deadly against the less wise.</P>
<P>However the fact remains that melees are very gear dependant, and such gear takes alot of time and effort to achieve...much more so than the average spell caster needs to PvP. It's pretty unfair to ask any pure melee to lose a BD bracer each time they PvP while pure casters only lose their cloth boots or highest pet spell. This breaks any balance resist gear gives and I'm against the full loot rule for this reason.</P>
<P>However, while playing on Discord I always believed that pure melees should have started with <STRONG>100MR+ </STRONG>extra because they could never hope to achieve balanced resists through gear. Perhaps such an idea could work on a harsh <STRONG>full loot </STRONG>server, in that pure melees are given higher starting resists.</P></FONT></DIV>	
