<img src="/eq/i/icons/Classes/shaman.gif" border=0 alt=""/></a><br>
			


			
			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=PVP&message.id=449#M449">60</a> of 127
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 454 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<P>"I'd rather find another way to directly reward PvP victors and punish the victims. Perhaps a TIME BASED penalty, where you are sent back to your bind with all you gear upon a PvP death but are unable to enter the zone of your death for say 5hours. This would really give the victors a feeling of reward, and at higher levels the winning guild could continue to raid without the typical zerg + training from the losers. The idea needs tweaking but you get the picture....."</P>
<P>- Darren</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>I posted a similar idea in the original 10 page thread about fixing PvP.&nbsp; In addition to adding a good reward for killing someone, I also&nbsp;like the idea because it removes bind rushing and corpse camping in one fell swoop, and PvP is more realistic from a roleplay perspective when the dead guy doesn't just come right back for more.&nbsp; I'm not sure how bad the coding would be to&nbsp;implement this though.&nbsp; It would have to be restricted to&nbsp;killshots by&nbsp;players, so non-killshot deaths would be one way of avoiding it (falling, running into mobs, removing hp item when low).&nbsp; One other thing that is a problem is when two raids are fairly well matched and are killing each other, the winning party would not have enough people who can enter the zone in order to complete the raid.&nbsp; To fix this, maybe give some kind of zone control switch where as soon as all people in zone are the same guild, other members of the same guild are free to zone in again.&nbsp; Also, since people are&nbsp;sometimes bound in the zone they die in, there would have to be alternate spawn points, maybe hometown newbie zones.</P>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
