<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=PVP&message.id=455#M455">62</a> of 127
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 425 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>You are definitely right that there are different schools of thought as to what makes a "good pvp server" - because as you point out, people have different ideas about what makes "good pvp".&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The way I look at it, is that there are already 3 "blue" pvp servers.&nbsp; TZ, VZ and RZ actually have very little pvp - and the pvp that does occur (especially on TZ) is "lame".&nbsp; People train, corpse camp, bind rush, etc.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Therefore, if you really want to diversify the pvp&nbsp;servers in terms of rules&nbsp;- and potentially attract&nbsp;PvPers to EQ, would be a server with rules like I outlined.&nbsp; The entire mindset of people who play on this server <EM>should </EM>change from "I'm looking for PvE most of the time and PvP when I feel it is convenient" to "I'm here to PvP non-stop - I only PvE so I'm not disadvantaged in PvP".&nbsp; Why camp loot through PvE when you can kill a guy and steal his FBSS?&nbsp; People should have far lower expectations for loot on a server with item loot - I don't see why this idea would be unpopular with people who really want to pvp.&nbsp; I welcome my losses, because they encourage me to do better, and they make my victories sweeter.&nbsp; What fun is there with no threat of loss and no competition (huge loot disparaties)?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><EM>Or long story short: a lot of people fear to be harassed when playing on a PvP server.<BR>The harder the punishment for PvP deaths the more effective harassing is possible.</EM></DIV>
<DIV><EM></EM>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Yes, harassment is "possible", on servers like this, but catering to people who complain about getting corpse camped once or losing an item should just stay on the blue server.&nbsp; If however, they decide that they'd like to try something different out, the option should be available.&nbsp; What are the person's expectations on this server?&nbsp; People should not have the mindset that they can go exp in peace and live happily ever after - the environment would (and should) be intense similar to the level of paranoia on Discord.&nbsp; However, I personally think real "harassment" actually would happen&nbsp;less on a "red" pvp server than it does on a "blue" pvp server in my opinion.&nbsp; Why?&nbsp; Because of the huge penalty for death - in this case, item loss.&nbsp; If someone is corpse camping you - call your guild in to come kill the person.&nbsp; The culprit wouldn't be wise to stay in one spot for long else the gank bus will run him over.&nbsp; If you are in a losing situation and there is no way to win for a while - log off.&nbsp; Come back later.&nbsp; Live to fight another day.&nbsp; That's what pvp <EM>should</EM> be about.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>In terms of "GvE" servers, I think that teams should be not necissarily based on diety - but rather simply color.&nbsp; Black / white, or red/blue.&nbsp; All classes and all races should be available to each team to promote balance, but the teams should be hardcoded.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
