		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<P>To refine my initial post, I would insert two additional rules to help balance pvp (specifically for the benefit of melees).</P>
<DIV><EM>4.)&nbsp; Enable item loot of one item per PvP death (even in bags) with the exception of epics - and remove no drop gear.&nbsp; Item loot is the second most important rule that can be implemented on this server (behind expansion choice), but it needs to also have the Firiona Vie ruleset where there are very very very few no drop items.&nbsp; To create a balance between those who PvE and those who PvP (and incentives for both groups), the ability to gain items and to lose items needs to be a real threat.&nbsp; </EM></DIV>
<DIV><EM>Now, in order to properly balance the server so melee classes are not hurt too badly by item loot, there should also be additional rules to help melees (but apply to all classes):</EM></DIV>
<DIV><EM>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Player can choose 2-4 items (dev discretion) that are unlootable upon death</EM></DIV>
<DIV><EM>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Or the only items not lootable upon death are epics (normal weapon slot items should be lootable.</EM></DIV>
<DIV><EM>I personally recommend the first solution.</EM></DIV>
<DIV><EM></EM>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Add:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV></DIV>	
