	<td bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	<td class="subjectbar" height="20" style="font-size: 8pt;padding-left:10px;" width="100%">
		Re: How to Fix EQ PvP - Address the real issue

	</td>
	
		<td class="subjectbar" align=right style="padding:0px;padding-right:10px;">












		<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 id="io_bpvpm520_table" 
		
			onClick="setId('520');showLiMenu(this,'io_bpvpm520','right',false);" 
			onDblClick="setId('520');showLiMenu(this,'io_bpvpm520','right',false);" 
			
		>
		<tr class=clickable>
			
				<td nowrap><a class=subjectbar_text style='font-size: 8pt;'>Options</a></td>
				
			<td>&nbsp;&nbsp;</td>
			<td><img src='/i/skins/default/button_options.gif' border=0 alt='Options' title='Options' width=11 height=28></td>
			<td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
		</table>
		
		</td></tr>
		
	<tr>
	
		<td class="msg_user_cell" width="150" valign=top>
		
			 









<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=25665'  class="auth_text"  style="font-weight:bold;" >	
<span style='color:#336600;'>Flaye</span></a>
			<br>
			
			<span style="font-size: 8pt;">
			Journeyman<br>
			
				Posts: 38<br>
				
				Registered: 04-15-2004
				
			</span>
			


			
			<br>
			
				<img src="/i/p.gif" height=8 width=150 border=0 alt=""><br>
				
			<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=25665'>







</a><br>
			


			
			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=PVP&message.id=520#M520">73</a> of 127
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 312 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>I played on Rallos Zek for a long time, &amp; I witnessed the entire evolution of the "item-loot vs no-item-loot" debate. I've been on both sides of it.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV></FONT></DIV>
<DIV>On one hand, I think that allowing for item loot is an implicit nerf of all equipment-necessary classes, &amp; by that, I mean the pure-melee classes in particular. The simple fact is that a melee class needs equipment to be effective, while a caster does not, &amp; that simple fact is precisely why Rallos Zek always had a reputation for being Naked Caster Heaven. Contrary to Trynd's assertion, it was NOT fun, &amp; frankly, I fail to see how any server that is nothing but Naked Caster Heaven could be fun -- except, of course, to the Naked Casters.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV></FONT></DIV>
<DIV>On the other hand: the removal of item loot -- ala' the three Baby Zeks -- means that melee classes can now happily spend tons of plats on hi-end resistance gear, armor, weapons, etc., knowing that their investment won't be taken from them. The addition of The Bazaar has made it easy for them to buy that gear, &amp; the prevalence of plat-buying gives them the money to do it. Now, you can say that all this is true of casters, too, except for one more simple fact: it's easier, by far, to twink a melee class for PvP than a caster, &amp; that's especially true if you're talking about a robe-caster.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV></FONT></DIV>
<DIV>I don't see any particular way to eliminate the conflict created by these points, but I will say that I suspect that eliminating item loot has solved more problems than it has caused.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV></FONT></DIV>
<DIV>I'm largely ambivalent about the suggestions Trynd made, but I think he began his analysis from a badly flawed premise -- i.e., the idea that the ONE reason people play on PvP servers is to face competition.&nbsp;I think that's overly simplistic; I'm quite sure that there are a lot of reasons people play on PvP servers. The ability to "b***h-gank" others &amp; generally grief lower-level players is certainly a reason, &amp; people who have that motivation -- those who willing to pay to play an inferior FPS game on slow, laggy servers, when they could be playing any number of much better FPS games on much better servers, &amp; without paying a penny for the service -- will be attracted to PvP servers no matter what rules-set is put in place. But I will say, flatly, that the addition of item loot -- no matter HOW you code it -- will attract such people far faster than will anything else, because now, not only can they "pwn" NooB1, they get some profit, as well.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV></FONT></DIV>
<DIV>There's a very, very good reason why the Zek servers are so under-populated, compared to the rest of the servers, &amp; it's NOT because people don't like PvP. Time &amp; time again, I've been told that people refuse to play on the Zeks, because they don't want to deal with a player base they believe is infested with misanthropic dorks. Eliminate the misanthropic dorks, &amp; you will improve EQ&nbsp;PvP&nbsp;dramatically. OTOH, I defy you to find a way to eliminate the misanthropic dorks. IMO, the&nbsp;PvP itself has NEVER been broken.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The players, OTOH, have been broken since&nbsp;Day 1, &amp; no patch is forth-coming.</FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
		<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
		 <span class=date_text>04-28-2004</span> <span class=time_text>07:52 AM</span>
		</span>
		</td>

		
